# Ripgrep-only ignores. Files here are tracked in git (so the plugin ships
# self-contained) but searching them is not useful.

# scripts/runtime/bin/*.js are esbuild bundles (single-line, ~200-500 KB).
# Grepping matches there surfaces 2 KB previews of compiled JS in the agent
# thread. Search scripts/runtime/engine/src/ for TypeScript source instead.
#
# Use a file pattern (not a directory pattern). `scripts/runtime/bin/` as a
# directory ignore hides only traversal matches; an explicit-path invocation
# like `rg foo scripts/runtime/bin/` still descended into the directory in
# some ripgrep versions, bypassing the ignore. Matching `*.js` directly keeps
# the directory visible but prevents any .js file inside from being searched.
# The `!*.sh` re-inclusion keeps shell shims greppable (currently empty set,
# but reserved for future scripts).
scripts/runtime/bin/*.js
!scripts/runtime/bin/*.sh
